Please help me develop a product image website using Next.js. The website should include the following:

- Company brand logo and slogan
- Product photos and specifications
- Product usage scenarios and examples
- Product features and advantages
- Customer reviews and case studies
- Customer service and contact information
- News updates and company events
- Contact us and join us options

Additional requirements:

1. Develop using SCSS
2. Develop using TypeScript
3. Integrate API using @reduxjs/toolkit
4. Use clsx and emotion libraries
5. Use Material-UI, but use SCSS for layout
6. Create versions for mobile, tablet, and desktop
7. Ensure proper SEO handling
8. Create apiSlice and generate test data using JSON placed in the config file
9. Organize page files in the `/src/pages` directory with corresponding SCSS and TSX files in the same folder

## File Structure

```
.
├── public
│   ├── index.html
│   ├── robots.txt
│   └── manifest.json
├── src
│   ├── react-app-env.d.ts
│   ├── App.tsx
│   ├── App.scss
│   ├── index.tsx
│   ├── assets
│   ├── components
│   ├── features
│   ├── hooks
│   ├── lib
│   ├── pages
│   ├── locales
│   ├── config
│   ├── types
│   │   ├── interfaces
│   │   │   └── index.ts
│   ├── utils
│   └── services
│       ├── api
│       │   └── apiSlice.ts
│       ├── middlewares
│       └── store.ts
├── .gitignore
├── .env.local
├── env.example
├── .tool-versions
├── tsconfig.json
├── package.json
└── README.md
```

Note: This is a suggested file structure for organizing your Next.js project. You can adjust it according to your specific needs.
